# Accessibility Guidelines

## Text Readability

- Maintain sufficient contrast between text and background
  - Primary text (white on dark background): minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio
  - Large text (>18pt): minimum 3:1 contrast ratio
- Use readable font sizes (minimum 14sp for normal text)
- Avoid relying solely on color to convey information

## Touch Targets

- All interactive elements should have a minimum touch target size of 44x44 points
- Provide sufficient spacing between touch targets (minimum 8px)
- Ensure buttons and controls have visible focus states

## Game Controls

- Support both gesture-based controls (swipe) and alternative input methods
- Consider adding button controls as an alternative to swipes
- Ensure game can be paused easily

## Visual Feedback

- Provide clear visual feedback for all interactions
- Use animations to reinforce actions and changes
- Ensure critical game information is not conveyed through color alone

## Settings

- Implement options to adjust or disable animations
- Consider adding high contrast mode
- Allow sound effects to be toggled on/off

## Testing

- Test the app with system font size adjustments
- Verify the app works well with screen readers
- Check that the game is playable without relying on color perception